article.description: Georgia Coach Andy Landers said Sherill Baker might have found her comfort zone in the second game of the season.
article.headline: Baker scores career-high 21 points
article.linkText: Baker finds a 'groove' for No. 10 Georgia's win
article.story:
STATESBORO, Ga. (AP) -- Georgia Coach Andy Landers said Sherill
Baker might have found her comfort zone in the second game of the
season.

He was less impressed with the overall performance of the No. 10
Lady Bulldogs in an 84-53 victory over Georgia Southern.

"I think Sherrill was just in a real groove tonight," Landers
said after Baker scored a career-high 21 points Tuesday night.
"She looked comfortable. She looked like she felt good."

Last season, Baker and Alexis Kendrick teamed to form an
all-freshman backcourt. Kendrick averaged 12.4 points, and Baker
9.6.

Landers said there was room for improvement.

Tuesday night, he said, "She got out on the open floor. That's
something we've encouraged her to do since we got her over a year
ago. Maybe tonight, she found that."

Georgia (2-0) got consecutive 3-pointers from Cori Chambers
during a 12-0 run that gave the Lady Bulldogs a 32-12 lead midway
through the first half.

Georgia led 39-23 at halftime. Kendrick opened the second half
with a 3-pointer and the Lady Bulldogs continued to pull away,
building the advantage to 77-49 on a layup by Baker with 3:33
remaining.

Jessica Everett led Georgia Southern (1-1) with 14 points, and
Shawnica Hill added 13.

Kara Braxton scored 11 points and had 12 rebounds for Georgia,
and Kendrick scored 12 points.

"Overall, you have to look at it and say it was a good win, but
there were some inconsistencies in there," Landers said.
"Tonight, I didn't see anything there that we can't improve.

"I think we have the abilities that we need. We just need to
keep working," he said.

Eagles coach Rusty Cram said, "You are never happy with a
loss."

But he said his team "played with a lot of effort, and I think
we learned a tremendous amount by playing a team with this type of
talent."
